It's a collection of atoms,
molecules, energy and motion,

00:31:48.540 --> 00:31:51.250 align:middle line:84%
all brought to life
in our imagination.

00:31:51.250 --> 00:31:54.060 align:middle line:10%
So if everything is brought
to life in our imagination,

00:31:54.060 --> 00:31:57.182 align:middle line:10%
then this cube also gives
us another valuable insight.

00:31:57.182 --> 00:31:58.890 align:middle line:10%
Because as you can
see, if you look at it

00:31:58.890 --> 00:32:00.640 align:middle line:10%
from one perspective,
it looks like you're

00:32:00.640 --> 00:32:02.510 align:middle line:10%
looking into the cube, right?

00:32:02.510 --> 00:32:04.080 align:middle line:10%
Then if you shift
your perspective,

00:32:04.080 --> 00:32:06.690 align:middle line:10%
now it looks like you're
looking down into the cube.

00:32:06.690 --> 00:32:08.880 align:middle line:10%
And a completely
different box appears.

00:32:08.880 --> 00:32:10.620 align:middle line:10%
Can you you all see
it shift or jump?

00:32:10.620 --> 00:32:14.700 align:middle line:84%
But to me, this cube
demonstrates or shows us the

00:32:14.700 --> 00:32:19.410 align:middle line:84%
only two ways that we
perceive everything out here.

00:32:19.410 --> 00:32:22.530 align:middle line:84%
Every single moment of our
lives, we're bringing things--

00:32:22.530 --> 00:32:24.730 align:middle line:84%
what's out here to life
in our imagination.

00:32:24.730 --> 00:32:26.500 align:middle line:90%
And we're making a choice.

00:32:26.500 --> 00:32:29.670 align:middle line:84%
Are we going to put fear
into what we're experiencing?

00:32:29.670 --> 00:32:32.980 align:middle line:84%
Or are we going to put love
into what we are experiencing?

00:32:32.980 --> 00:32:33.780 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:32:33.780 --> 00:32:37.560 align:middle line:84%
Those are the only two choices
we have every single moment

00:32:37.560 --> 00:32:38.800 align:middle line:90%
of our lives.

00:32:38.800 --> 00:32:42.690 align:middle line:84%
And so if love, peace, joy,
happiness, wholeness, holiness,

00:32:42.690 --> 00:32:45.105 align:middle line:84%
perfection, 360, "I
am-plus" is our goal.

00:32:45.105 --> 00:32:47.730 align:middle line:84%
And we're down here going, well,
I'm not sure if I can do that.

00:32:47.730 --> 00:32:51.960 align:middle line:84%
And, oh, I've got an appointment
in five minutes-- or whatever.

00:32:51.960 --> 00:32:54.240 align:middle line:84%
We're not going to
get there, right?

00:32:54.240 --> 00:32:56.400 align:middle line:84%
Because the golden rule
says what we put out

00:32:56.400 --> 00:32:57.810 align:middle line:90%
is what we get back.

00:32:57.810 --> 00:32:59.880 align:middle line:84%
So our goal-- and
this is, I think,

00:32:59.880 --> 00:33:02.970 align:middle line:84%
one of the most important
reasons why we incarnate

00:33:02.970 --> 00:33:05.880 align:middle line:84%
on Earth is it's a sort of
a cosmic kindergarten for us

00:33:05.880 --> 00:33:08.820 align:middle line:84%
to manifest or
understand this principle

00:33:08.820 --> 00:33:11.430 align:middle line:84%
and how powerful our
thoughts and emotions are.

00:33:11.430 --> 00:33:15.480 align:middle line:84%
Because as we've noticed, our
world is accelerating, right?

00:33:15.480 --> 00:33:19.535 align:middle line:10%
And if you can't handle your
emotions now, what do you think

00:33:19.535 --> 00:33:20.910 align:middle line:10%
is going to happen
in a few years

00:33:20.910 --> 00:33:23.740 align:middle line:10%
when we're screaming
down the highway?

00:33:23.740 --> 00:33:24.540 align:middle line:10%
Right?

00:33:24.540 --> 00:33:27.540 align:middle line:10%
This is why this is so important
for us to get a handle on.

00:33:27.540 --> 00:33:30.990 align:middle line:10%
Because the idea is that as
we expand in our awareness

00:33:30.990 --> 00:33:33.570 align:middle line:10%
and consciousness, our
three-dimensional cube

00:33:33.570 --> 00:33:36.990 align:middle line:10%
which represents our
world becomes the core

00:33:36.990 --> 00:33:39.210 align:middle line:10%
of a fourth-dimensional
hypercube

00:33:39.210 --> 00:33:41.010 align:middle line:10%
with all kinds of
parallel worlds

00:33:41.010 --> 00:33:43.500 align:middle line:10%
suddenly impinging on our
consciousness and all kinds

00:33:43.500 --> 00:33:46.530 align:middle line:10%
of opportunities for expanding
our consciousness being

00:33:46.530 --> 00:33:47.670 align:middle line:10%
presented to ourselves.

00:33:47.670 --> 00:33:49.450 align:middle line:10%
Does that makes sense?

00:33:49.450 --> 00:33:54.240 align:middle line:10%
So this is where many of us
are already at right now.

00:33:54.240 --> 00:33:56.880 align:middle line:90%
We've transcended the 3D world.

00:33:56.880 --> 00:34:00.340 align:middle line:84%
And now we're going into
the 4D and five 3D world.

00:34:00.340 --> 00:34:03.080 align:middle line:84%
And so those are
the pioneers that

00:34:03.080 --> 00:34:05.820 align:middle line:84%
are mastering the power of
their thought and emotion

00:34:05.820 --> 00:34:10.830 align:middle line:84%
and recognizing the illusory
nature of our world.

00:34:10.830 --> 00:34:13.830 align:middle line:84%
You've heard of living
outside the box.

00:34:13.830 --> 00:34:18.540 align:middle line:84%
The ascended beings live as
if there is no box, right?

00:34:18.540 --> 00:34:19.560 align:middle line:90%
That's the big flip.

00:34:19.560 --> 00:34:21.120 align:middle line:84%
That's one way
you will know when

00:34:21.120 --> 00:34:23.699 align:middle line:84%
you have accomplished
your ascension is you're

00:34:23.699 --> 00:34:25.840 align:middle line:90%
no longer living in the box.

00:34:25.840 --> 00:34:29.219 align:middle line:84%
So to the question-- when
did this illusion begin?

00:34:29.219 --> 00:34:31.320 align:middle line:10%
Well, Buddhism teaches
that the second we

00:34:31.320 --> 00:34:34.620 align:middle line:10%
veiled our pure Buddha nature,
our rainbow light body,

00:34:34.620 --> 00:34:37.750 align:middle line:10%
with a fundamental
mistake, the notion of "I,"

00:34:37.750 --> 00:34:40.110 align:middle line:10%
and separated ourselves
from everything out here,

00:34:40.110 --> 00:34:41.847 align:middle line:10%
that's when the illusion began.

00:34:41.847 --> 00:34:43.139 align:middle line:10%
That's when the illusion began.

00:34:43.139 --> 00:34:45.630 align:middle line:10%
We are taught, I am
separate from this stage,

00:34:45.630 --> 00:34:48.300 align:middle line:10%
from this chair, from my
computer, and so forth.

00:34:48.300 --> 00:34:51.760 align:middle line:10%
But really, we're
all the same thing.

00:34:51.760 --> 00:34:54.030 align:middle line:10%
All indeed one.

00:34:54.030 --> 00:34:57.990 align:middle line:84%
Creation is happening
at every single second.

00:34:57.990 --> 00:35:01.260 align:middle line:84%
And that is what starts
to give us some--

00:35:01.260 --> 00:35:05.520 align:middle line:84%
if I can use the word control
or ability to navigate

00:35:05.520 --> 00:35:07.290 align:middle line:90%
this illusory realm.

00:35:07.290 --> 00:35:09.683 align:middle line:84%
In the Buddhist view, there
are three kinds of dreams--

00:35:09.683 --> 00:35:11.100 align:middle line:84%
the dream of
nighttime, which ends

00:35:11.100 --> 00:35:14.400 align:middle line:84%
with daylight, the
dream of Earth lifetime,

00:35:14.400 --> 00:35:18.840 align:middle line:84%
which ends with death, and the
dream of ignorance or samsara,

00:35:18.840 --> 00:35:21.090 align:middle line:90%
which ends with enlightenment.

00:35:21.090 --> 00:35:22.770 align:middle line:84%
And that is our
goal-- enlightenment

00:35:22.770 --> 00:35:26.250 align:middle line:84%
and ascension are
essentially synonymous.

00:35:26.250 --> 00:35:30.120 align:middle line:10%
The way out is to wake
up completely returned

00:35:30.120 --> 00:35:33.420 align:middle line:10%
to our true nature as
rainbow light body beings

00:35:33.420 --> 00:35:34.920 align:middle line:10%
as it was in the
original beginning,

00:35:34.920 --> 00:35:38.580 align:middle line:10%
before the "I" separated us
from everything out here.

00:35:38.580 --> 00:35:40.800 align:middle line:10%
And we became deeply
lost or enmeshed

00:35:40.800 --> 00:35:43.470 align:middle line:10%
in this illusory world.

00:35:43.470 --> 00:35:45.960 align:middle line:10%
And there are many ways
to remind ourselves

00:35:45.960 --> 00:35:50.700 align:middle line:10%
of our true nature of our
rainbow light body selves.

00:35:50.700 --> 00:35:56.100 align:middle line:84%
Among them are meditation,
prayers, recitation of mantras,

00:35:56.100 --> 00:35:59.700 align:middle line:84%
construction of inspiring
or sacred places,

00:35:59.700 --> 00:36:03.300 align:middle line:84%
visiting sacred places, which
is why my wife Claire and I

00:36:03.300 --> 00:36:06.950 align:middle line:84%
love taking people to
England, Italy, France, Egypt.

00:36:06.950 --> 00:36:11.280 align:middle line:10%
Going to Israel later this
year to walk in these paths.

00:36:11.280 --> 00:36:14.310 align:middle line:10%
Because we know that connecting
with these sacred places

00:36:14.310 --> 00:36:15.690 align:middle line:10%
feeds our light body.

00:36:15.690 --> 00:36:17.718 align:middle line:10%
That's why we go, right?

00:36:17.718 --> 00:36:19.260 align:middle line:10%
It's not to have a
wonderful holiday.

00:36:19.260 --> 00:36:22.590 align:middle line:84%
It's to feed our souls
and awaken our light body.

00:36:22.590 --> 00:36:24.900 align:middle line:84%
But above all,
according to Buddhism,

00:36:24.900 --> 00:36:28.500 align:middle line:84%
the number one way
to remind yourself

00:36:28.500 --> 00:36:31.740 align:middle line:84%
of your true nature,
your light body self,

00:36:31.740 --> 00:36:35.370 align:middle line:90%
is meditation on sacred images.

00:36:35.370 --> 00:36:36.390 align:middle line:90%
It's not my opinion.

00:36:36.390 --> 00:36:39.430 align:middle line:10%
This is what the Buddhism--
teaching a very long time.

00:36:39.430 --> 00:36:41.730 align:middle line:10%
So for example, this image
of the standing Buddha

00:36:41.730 --> 00:36:44.080 align:middle line:10%
is a good example
where the Buddha

00:36:44.080 --> 00:36:47.880 align:middle line:10%
has got his palm open to you,
transmitting frequencies,

00:36:47.880 --> 00:36:51.290 align:middle line:10%
vibrations of your
true nature to you.

00:36:51.290 --> 00:36:55.560 align:middle line:84%
In the yogic tradition,
they call this ekagrata,

00:36:55.560 --> 00:37:00.420 align:middle line:84%
or one pointedness
meditation on sacred images.

00:37:00.420 --> 00:37:03.210 align:middle line:90%
When the devotee-- you and I--

00:37:03.210 --> 00:37:08.100 align:middle line:84%
places our self before a sacred
image, the task of the devotee

00:37:08.100 --> 00:37:12.450 align:middle line:84%
is to recognize the
illusory division between us

00:37:12.450 --> 00:37:18.570 align:middle line:84%
and the deity ourselves and
to transcend that illusion.

00:37:18.570 --> 00:37:23.280 align:middle line:10%
And in so doing, we are
connected with the Buddha.

00:37:23.280 --> 00:37:25.170 align:middle line:10%
And when we
single-mindedly contemplate

00:37:25.170 --> 00:37:27.660 align:middle line:10%
on the magnificence
of the Buddha's image,

00:37:27.660 --> 00:37:30.420 align:middle line:10%
we are practicing,
as I said, ekagrata.

00:37:30.420 --> 00:37:33.720 align:middle line:84%
And when we do this
repeatedly over time,

00:37:33.720 --> 00:37:36.690 align:middle line:84%
the image of the Buddha
stays constantly in our mind.

00:37:36.690 --> 00:37:39.630 align:middle line:10%
We are rewiring
our brain to match

00:37:39.630 --> 00:37:42.240 align:middle line:10%
the frequency of the Buddha.

00:37:42.240 --> 00:37:44.070 align:middle line:10%
This is how they would do it.

00:37:44.070 --> 00:37:48.480 align:middle line:10%
No texts involved, just simple
contemplation, meditation,

00:37:48.480 --> 00:37:50.340 align:middle line:10%
and reflection on the
image of the Buddha

00:37:50.340 --> 00:37:53.850 align:middle line:10%
until your brain is so
connected with that,

00:37:53.850 --> 00:37:57.190 align:middle line:10%
that you actually become it.

00:37:57.190 --> 00:37:59.830 align:middle line:84%
How much easier do
you want it to be?

00:37:59.830 --> 00:38:00.730 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:38:00.730 --> 00:38:02.620 align:middle line:84%
Who needs to sit in
a cave for 40 years?

00:38:02.620 --> 00:38:03.420 align:middle line:90%
You don't need to.

00:38:03.420 --> 00:38:06.460 align:middle line:84%
You just need to get the right
images in your consciousness

00:38:06.460 --> 00:38:09.250 align:middle line:84%
and rewire your
brain to match what

00:38:09.250 --> 00:38:11.930 align:middle line:90%
we are seeing in these images.

00:38:11.930 --> 00:38:13.262 align:middle line:90%
This is a major practice.

00:38:13.262 --> 00:38:15.220 align:middle line:84%
And the Tibetans actually--
they call it merit.

00:38:15.220 --> 00:38:19.770 align:middle line:84%
You're getting merit every time
you look at a sacred image.

00:38:19.770 --> 00:38:23.080 align:middle line:84%
If you finance a sacred image,
if you visit a sacred place,

00:38:23.080 --> 00:38:26.290 align:middle line:84%
you're gaining merit,
both in this life

00:38:26.290 --> 00:38:31.330 align:middle line:84%
and in future incarnations,
wherever that may be.

00:38:31.330 --> 00:38:33.670 align:middle line:84%
The Buddhists also teach
that to achieve illumination

00:38:33.670 --> 00:38:35.380 align:middle line:84%
or experience Buddha
nature, we must

00:38:35.380 --> 00:38:37.360 align:middle line:84%
meditate on the
blue pearl, which

00:38:37.360 --> 00:38:38.980 align:middle line:90%
is here in our pineal gland.

00:38:38.980 --> 00:38:41.253 align:middle line:84%
They call it the jewel in
the heart of the lotus.

00:38:41.253 --> 00:38:43.045 align:middle line:84%
This is the meaning of
the Buddhist mantra,

00:38:43.045 --> 00:38:45.480 align:middle line:90%
Om mani padme hum.

00:38:45.480 --> 00:38:48.220 align:middle line:84%
Om mani padme hum,
which is a mantra

00:38:48.220 --> 00:38:52.510 align:middle line:84%
that you can chant as you are
meditating on these images.

